campaign_assets.name: removeContacts_message
campaign_assets.value:
Contact lenses alter the thin tear layer on your cornea. To ensure accurate exam results, your eyes need 15 minutes to return to their natural state.

If you need glasses to see, please wear them until we ask you to remove them in a few minutes.

You will be able to use your contact lenses after the exam ends

campaign_assets.value: This medical app tests for refractive errors within these ranges: Sphere power: -1.00 D to -5.00 D Cylinder power: up to -2.00 D Total combined power: up to -6.00 D The user’s results and medical history are then reviewed by a licensed eye care professional, who issues a prescription if necessary.

campaign_assets.name: examCompletion_subTitle
campaign_assets.value: We have collected your vision exam data, which can now be used by an eye care professional to issue your Rx.

campaign_assets.name: examCompletion_qAndA_question1
campaign_assets.value: Do I need a yearly eye exam?

campaign_assets.name: examCompletion_qAndA_answer1
campaign_assets.value: The long answer is that it depends. For most healthy people, you don't need an eye exam every year. The American Academy of Ophthalmology recommends getting an exam based on your medical conditions and age. That can be as little as one to two times in your twenties and thirties, a comprehensive exam at 40, and then yearly exams after 65. It's best to check with your eye care professional to determine how often you need a comprehensive exam.

campaign_assets.name: examCompletion_qAndA_answer2
campaign_assets.value:
You may also consider going in for an eye exam if you believe your prescription has changed. There are many signs to watch out for that might indicate that your prescription might need to be updated. Even if your prescription is perfect, the specific lens you were prescribed may be giving you trouble.  
If you experience any of the following symptoms, we'd always recommend booking an appointment to consult with an eye doctor.

campaign_assets.name: examCompletion_qAndA_answer3
campaign_assets.value: Yes! If you don't have a history of eye related to health problems and are happy with your current prescription, then you may be eligible for our ExpressExam. It's a super-simple way to renew your contact lens prescription online. While it is not a comprehensive eye exam, it is a vision exam that lets you quickly assess whether it's time for a prescription change.
